<title>GERMANY: Opel-GM puts Lopez legal costs at 10 million marks.</title>
<headline>Opel-GM puts Lopez legal costs at 10 million marks.</headline>
<dateline>RUESSELSHEIM, Germany 1997-01-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Adam Opel AG, the German unit of U.S. carmaker General Motors AG, said that legal costs in the long-running legal dispute with Volkswagen amounted to 10 million marks ($6.3 million).</p>
<p>&quot;The legal costs for GM-Opel are around ten million deutschemarks,&quot; said Adam Opel management board chairman David Herman at a news conference.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525 ($ = 1.577 German Marks)</p>
